definition.value: A purine 2'-deoxyribonucleoside 5'-monophosphate having guanine as the nucleobase.
A monohydroxybenzoate that is the conjugate base of 3-hydroxybenzoic acid.
A monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of bispyribac, arising from the deprotonation of the carboxy group. Major species at pH 7.3.
An octadec-9-enoic acid in which the double bond at C-9 has Z (cis) stereochemistry.
